the greatest is a 1977 film about the life of boxer muhammad ali , in which ali plays himself . it was directed by tom gries and monte hellman . the film follows ali 's life from the 1960 olympics to his regaining the heavyweight crown from george foreman in their famous " rumble in the jungle " fight in 1974 . the footage of the boxing matches themselves are largely the actual footage from the time involved . the movie is based on the book the greatest : my own story written by muhammad ali and richard durham and edited by toni morrison . the song " the greatest love of all " was written for this film and sung by george benson ; it was later covered by whitney houston .